{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784095970989,"sessionID":"ses_09ba79b75ffeDs2zUUPi2ip2Dh","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"Y67o86WBLMm4ftqSyu3wRa0PMiQX5Cql","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Find interpolation constant","prompt":"Search the Go repository for constants or variables related to interpolation. Look for any constants that might indicate when interpolation is needed. Search through the codebase for patterns like \"interpolation\", \"need\", \"required\", or other related terms. Return the exact package, symbol name, and position of any constants you find that might be related to interpolation.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_09ba50b1fffeaqJkc1ab7T67pj (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nBased on my comprehensive search of the Go repository, I have found the following constants related to interpolation:\n\n## Constants Related to Interpolation\n\n### 1. `internal/kms/query.go`\n\n**`updateCompletedCountQueryTemplate`** (lines 28-37)\n- **Type**: `string` (SQL query template)\n- **Description**: Used to update the completed count for a specific table after running. Contains an interpolated variable for the table name.\n- **Code**:\n  ```go\n  updateCompletedCountQueryTemplate = `\n  update kms_data_key_version_destruction_job_run\n  set\n      is_running=false,\n      completed_count=(\n          total_count-(select count(*) from %q where key_id=@key_id)\n      )\n  where\n      key_id=@key_id and table_name=@table_name\n  `\n  ```\n- **Comments**: \"The interpolated variable is the table name.\"\n\n**`findAffectedRowsForKeyQueryTemplate`** (line 72)\n- **Type**: `string` (SQL query template)\n- **Description**: Used to find rows encrypted with a specific data key version ID in a table. Contains an interpolated variable for the table name.\n- **Code**:\n  ```go\n  findAffectedRowsForKeyQueryTemplate = `select count(*) from %q where key_id=?`\n  ```\n- **Comments**: \"The interpolated variable is the table name.\"\n\n## Summary\n\nThe search found **2 constants** in the `internal/kms/query.go` package that are SQL query templates with interpolated variables:\n\n1. `updateCompletedCountQueryTemplate` - lines 28-37\n2. `findAffectedRowsForKeyQueryTemplate` - line 72\n\nBoth constants contain SQL templates using `%q` placeholders for table names that are interpolated at runtime. No other constants or variables were found that explicitly indicate when interpolation is needed.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_09ba50b1fffeaqJkc1ab7T67pj","model":{"modelID":"unsloth/GLM-4.7-Flash-GGUF:UD-Q4_K_XL","providerID":"local"},"truncated":false},"title":"Find interpolation constant","time":{"start":1784095110383,"end":1784095970989}},"id":"prt_f645ab8fc001nlU8RaibVtqJWt","sessionID":"ses_09ba79b75ffeDs2zUUPi2ip2Dh","messageID":"msg_f645a988b001JBimvttngcXc2f"}}
